page.title: 18WILD FLOWERS IN STUDLEY WOOD
page.content: JUNE 6th. Bluebell, Bugle, Bush Vetch, Creeping & Common Buttercup, Cowslip, Cuckoo Pint,Dog's Mercury,Forget-me-not Hedge Parsley,Herb Bennet, Herb Robert, Horehound, Lady's Smock, Ragged Robin, Lesser Stitchwort,Lesser Yellow Trefoil Wood Spurge, Yellow Archangel. JULY 11th. Bird's Foot Trefoil,Bramble, Bittersweet, Bush Vetch,Creeping B'cup, Creeping Cinquefoil, Forget-me-not, Common Spotted Orchis, Hedge Woundwort, Enchanter's Nightshade, Honeysuckle, Hairy St.John's Wort, Herb Robert, Lesser Yellow Trefoil, Meadowseet, Meadow Vetchling, Mouse Ear Chickweed, Nipplewort,Self Heal,Scarce Willowherb, Silver Weed, Slender Bedstraw, White Clover & White Field Rose. June 1985 was extremely wet & cold with little sunshine. July started hot but rain & cold weather returned. Conditions underfoot were very wet.
